      {
        q: 'Can I build custom playlists?',
        a: 'Yes. Save practices to a custom list — by topic, season, or unit — and play them in any order. Playlists are shareable with colleagues at the same school.',
      },
      {
        q: 'Who creates the content?',
        a: 'Our content team is led by certified mindfulness instructors with classroom teaching backgrounds, reviewed by a clinical advisory board, and tested with real teachers before release.',
      },
      {
        q: 'Are there practices for hard days?',
        aHtml:
          'Yes. Look for the <em>Steady</em> collection: short, grounding practices for use after fire drills, community loss, difficult news, or any day a class needs extra care.',
      },
      {
        q: 'Does Inner Explorer align with state SEL standards?',
        aHtml:
          'Yes — our library is mapped to CASEL’s five core competencies and to most state-specific SEL frameworks. Mapping documents are available in the resource library for download.',
      },
      {
        q: 'Do you offer holiday or seasonal content?',
        a: 'Yes — secular practices anchored to the school-year calendar: back-to-school, testing weeks, transitions, and end of year. Nothing is tied to any one religious tradition.',
      },
      {
        q: 'Can I preview a practice before playing it for students?',
        a: 'Always. Every practice page has a preview button, and you can read the full transcript before pressing play in front of a class.',
